Distribution. The species complex occurs from the Iberian Peninsula to Japan and has a continuous range throughout N China (
Fig. 20
). In North America , it was introduced to Pennsylvania in the 1880 s (
Casey 1892
) and to California in the late 1930 s (
Van Dyke 1950
). The two introduced populations dispersed rapidly, merged in the 1960 s or 70 s at the latest and reached Manitoba, New Brunswick, Ontario and Québec in Canada (
McNamara 1991
;
Webster et al . 2012
).
